Vheadline
p2
VTribute to Dikshitar
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe audience was spellbound as musicians from various parts of the country sang compositions of Muthuswami Dikshitar, youngest of the  Music Trinity, at his memorial at Ettayapuram, in Tuticorin District, on August 10.The event, &#8216;Musical Tribute to Muthuswami Dikshitar,&#8217; was jointly organised by Sri Parthasarathi Swami Sabha, Saraswathi Vaggeyakara Trust, Narada Gana Sabha, Bharatiya Sangeetha Vaibavam (all based in Chennai) and Sri Nadhajyothi Muthuswami Dikshitar Memorial Trust, Ettayapuram.&#8220;We have been organising  musical tributes for the past 20 years at Ettayapuram, where Dikshitar breathed his last, &#8221; M. Krishnamurthy, secretary, Sri Parthasarathi Swami Sabha, said.A total of 49 compositions of Dikshitar sung by Seetha Narayanan, Prema Rangarajan, T.H.Thyagarajan, Kausalya, P. Venkatraman, Amritha Murali, Lakshmi Sriram, Padmini Ravi and Lalitha Santhanam,  and Purnima Krishnan (from Mumbai) was  a soothing  aural experience for  music lovers.The vocalists were accompanied by Thiruvallur V. Parthasarathy, Sriram Kumar, Tiruchi Govindarajan and Amritha Murali on the violin, and Ramanathapuram V. Ramanathan, Manikudi Chandrasekhar and Nanganallur Sriram on the mridangam.The concert began with &#8216;Siddhi Vinayagam...&#8217; in Roopaka talam,  by Seetha Narayanan, and concluded  with &#8216;Mayee...&#8217;  in Adi, sung by Lalitha Santhanam.
